  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Electrical Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Our esteemed client in the <strong>Electrical Engineering industry</strong> is seeking an <strong>Project Engineer </strong>to join their dynamic team:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Permanent</li>\n  <li><strong>Position:</strong> Electrical Project Engineer (M&amp;E / ELV)</li>\n  <li><strong>Location:</strong> Islandwide (depends on project’s location)</li>\n  <li><strong>Working Hours:</strong> 5.5 days (Mon to Fri, 9am to 6pm; Sat, 9am to 1pm)</li>\n  <li><strong>Salary Package:</strong> Up to $4,800 + Bonus</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide technical support and assist the Project Manager in project planning, coordination, and execution of all site activities.</li>\n  <li>Prepare, review, and update engineering documents such as drawings, method statements, risk assessments, safe work procedures, and operation &amp; maintenance manuals.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and supervise construction teams and subcontractors in the installation, testing, and commissioning of electrical and ELV systems to meet specifications and quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with consultants, clients, and relevant authorities on engineering and technical matters.</li>\n  <li>Plan and schedule site work activities according to the master program to ensure timely and safe completion.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with safety, quality, and regulatory requirements throughout the project lifecycle.</li>\n  <li>Perform ad-hoc duties as assigned by Management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least Diploma in Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering or related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of experience in Electrical or M&amp;E construction projects.</li>\n  <li>Good understanding of electrical installation, testing, and commissioningworks.</li>\n  <li>Able to interpret technical drawings and specifications accurately.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with local codes, standards, and safety regulations.</li>\n  <li>Able to work at different site locationsand adapt to dynamic project environments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Ready to apply? Here’s how:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Click the APPLY button, or</li>\n  <li>Email your resume (in MS Word or PDF format) to <a href=\"mailto:adelin@intuitrecruitment.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>adelin@intuitrecruitment.com</strong>.</a> Include the job title in your email subject line for prompt processing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></em></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>By submitting your application, you consent to the collection and use of your personal data under Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA).</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Adelin Chong | EA Personnel Reg No.: R1875641</p>\n<p>Intuit Recruitment Pte Ltd | EA License No.: 25C2793</p>",
